going on over there.

172
00:09:26,064 --> 00:09:27,364
- Over where?

173
00:09:27,365 --> 00:09:28,466
- [Chiaki] Over there.

174
00:09:29,567 --> 00:09:31,002
Look, you see it?

175
00:09:34,038 --> 00:09:35,038
- Yes!

176
00:09:35,874 --> 00:09:36,808
- [Maya] What's wrong?

177
00:09:36,809 --> 00:09:39,042
Aren't you enjoying yourself?

178
00:09:39,043 --> 00:09:42,579
- Well, it's just that
I'm not bored or anything.

179
00:09:42,580 --> 00:09:44,682
I think what's starting
to bug me is that,

180
00:09:45,817 --> 00:09:47,251
is that I'd rather be practicing

181
00:09:47,252 --> 00:09:49,286
than just hanging out like this.

182
00:09:49,287 --> 00:09:52,256
I know I've got a long way to
go before I'm as good as you,

183
00:09:52,257 --> 00:09:55,960
but still, I think that I'm
at least getting a bit closer.

184
00:09:58,630 --> 00:10:00,097
- They say it's
best to cast away

185
00:10:00,098 --> 00:10:02,132
the anguish and start anew.

186
00:10:02,133 --> 00:10:04,735
Resting to regain one's
spirit is an important part

187
00:10:04,736 --> 00:10:06,504
of the training
process, as well.

188
00:10:07,839 --> 00:10:10,107
Your fists are especially
damaged right now.

189
00:10:10,108 --> 00:10:12,376
It's important you
take care of them.

190
00:10:12,377 --> 00:10:15,312
(humming noise)

191
00:10:15,313 --> 00:10:17,981
- Hey, what the hell are
you tryin' to do to my hand?

192
00:10:17,982 --> 00:10:20,817
- I'm helping them heal by
channeling my Chi into them.

193
00:10:20,818 --> 00:10:23,954
- My hands'll be just
fine on their own, thanks!

194
00:10:23,955 --> 00:10:26,691
(plane whooshes)

195
00:10:29,627 --> 00:10:32,029
- [Passerby 1] All right,
you ready for some bowling?

196
00:10:32,030 --> 00:10:34,966
- [Passerby 2] Sure, but the
loser's gotta pick up the tab.

197
00:10:37,936 --> 00:10:40,604
- Sorry, gentlemen, but
we have just closed up.

198
00:10:40,605 --> 00:10:43,241
Please come back during
our normal business hours.

199
00:10:44,876 --> 00:10:46,344
- Let's go someplace else.

200
00:10:47,712 --> 00:10:50,014
- [Passerby] That really
throws a wrench into our night.

201
00:10:52,116 --> 00:10:53,917
(muffled struggling noises)

202
00:10:53,918 --> 00:10:56,586
- [Female Voice]
Hey, what's going on?

203
00:10:56,587 --> 00:10:59,556
- I'm tired of waiting around,
let's go someplace else.

204
00:10:59,557 --> 00:11:00,691
- Yeah, what's the deal?

205
00:11:00,692 --> 00:11:02,159
Isn't anybody
working here tonight?

206
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:03,561
- What's up with this place?

207
00:11:08,666 --> 00:11:10,734
(water dripping)

208
00:11:10,735 --> 00:11:11,968
(sad violin music)

209
00:11:11,969 --> 00:11:13,637
- [Aya Voiceover]
I know I can do it.

210
00:11:13,638 --> 00:11:16,274
I don't have any other
use for this power.

211
00:11:18,776 --> 00:11:20,711
I know they say
that it can be used

212
00:11:20,712 --> 00:11:23,014
to see thousands
of leagues away,

213
00:11:24,415 --> 00:11:27,552
but I just want to know
about Souichiro Sama.

214
00:11:31,689 --> 00:11:34,458
(water drips)

215
00:11:34,459 --> 00:11:35,459
I know I can.

216
00:11:36,160 --> 00:11:37,595
I know I can do it.

217
00:11:38,729 --> 00:11:40,730
- If you hadn't claimed
him as your fiance,

218
00:11:40,731 --> 00:11:43,200
I may have fallen
in love with him.

219
00:11:43,201 --> 00:11:46,803
(heartbeat sounds)

220
00:11:46,804 --> 00:11:49,773
- [Aya Voiceover] I'm sorry
for cheating like this, sis.

221
00:11:49,774 --> 00:11:52,844
I want to trust you, I
really do, but, but I...

222
00:11:55,847 --> 00:11:58,481
At the very least,
let me see that night.

223
00:11:58,482 --> 00:12:00,584
I just want to see that night.

224
00:12:00,585 --> 00:12:03,954
That's all I ask,
please, show me.

225
00:12:03,955 --> 00:12:06,923
(air whooshing)

226
00:12:06,924 --> 00:12:08,892
(water drips)

227
